      "description": "Execute a shell command in the host machine's terminal. Commands run in the current working directory by default. Returns stdout and stderr with a footer showing exit code and elapsed time. The working directory persists between commands; shell state does not. Does not support interactive commands.\n\nGuidance:\n- File search: Read file contents with Read, explore directories with Bash commands (ls, find, tree)\n- Content search: Use commands via Bash\n- Read files: Use Read tool, not cat/head/tail\n- Edit files: Use Edit tool, not sed/awk\n- Write files: Use Write tool, not echo/cat\n\nNote: Shell interprets backticks (`) and $() inside double-quoted arguments as command substitution.\n",
